The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 11 October is 514,439 (914 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 October, there were 81,594 new confirmed cases (145.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 September, there were 51,689 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 58% (29,905 extra cases).
